subject: Add Redfish EnvironmentMetrics schema in bmcweb
commitMessage:
Add Redfish EnvironmentMetrics schema in bmcweb

The EnvironmentMetrics is a new resource in Redfish version 2020.4.
This resource shall represent the environmental metrics for a
Redfish implementation.

This resource includes Energy consumption,Fan speeds (percent),
Power consumption (Watts), etc.And these data are mainly obtained
from under sensors.

ref:
https://redfish.dmtf.org/schemas/v1/EnvironmentMetrics.v1_0_0.json

Tested: Validator passes
After booting
1.doGet method to get EnvironmentMetrics

 curl -k -H "X-Auth-Token: $token" -X GET https://${bmc}/redfish/v1/Chassis/chassis/EnvironmentMetrics
{
  "@odata.id": "/redfish/v1/Chassis/chassis/EnvironmentMetrics",
  "@odata.type": "#EnvironmentMetrics.v1_0_0.EnvironmentMetrics",
  "FanSpeedsPercent": [
    {
      "@odata.id": "/redfish/v1/Chassis/chassis/Sensors/fan0_0",
      "DataSourceUri": "/redfish/v1/Chassis/chassis/Sensors/fan0_0",
      "DeviceName": "Chassis Fan #fan0_0",

    },

    },
    {

      "DataSourceUri": "/redfish/v1/Chassis/chassis/Sensors/fan1_1",
      "DeviceName": "Chassis Fan #fan1_1",
      "SpeedRPM": -110.0

{

    {

    {

  ],

}
2.Enter the wrong chassisId with the doGet method

 curl -k -H "X-Auth-Token: $token" -X GET https://${bmc}/redfish/v1/Chassis/chassisERROR/EnvironmentMetrics
{
  "error": {
    "@Message.ExtendedInfo": [
      {
        "@odata.type": "#Message.v1_1_1.Message",
        "Message": "The requested resource of type Chassis named chassisERROR was not found.",
        "MessageArgs": [
          "Chassis",
          "chassisERROR"
        ],
        "MessageId": "Base.1.8.1.ResourceNotFound",
        "MessageSeverity": "Critical",
        "Resolution": "Provide a valid resource identifier and resubmit the request."
      }
    ],
    "code": "Base.1.8.1.ResourceNotFound",
    "message": "The requested resource of type Chassis named chassisERROR was not found."
  }
}

From the documentation, EnvironmentMetrics does not exist only under Chassis. At least the example given in the document is /system/<systemId>/Processors/<Id>/EnvironmentMetrics, isn't it?
What is needed at present is EnvironmentMetrics under chassis. If there are related needs in the future, then add EnvironmentMetrics under other paths.

ok, I get it.
My other meaning is that the /chassis/.../EnvironmentMetrics path should be implemented in chassis.hpp, not in this file.

And this class name can be changed to ChassisEnvironmentMetrics. Considering that this Schema will be implemented in other paths in the future.

Then environment_metrics.hpp should move to redfish-core/include/utils. Refer to it in the header of the chassis.hpp file like collection.hpp.

EnvironmentMetrics  can be in multiple places: 
From https://redfish.dmtf.org/schemas/v1/EnvironmentMetrics_v1.xml
...
<String>/redfish/v1/Chassis/{ChassisId}/EnvironmentMetrics</String>
...

For example, suppose we want to add'/redfish/v1/System/<systemId>/Memory/<memoryId>/EnvironmentMetrics' in the future.
The EnvironmentMetrics class needs to be completely refactored. Complete the URL with incoming parameters so that it can be used in multiple places?

Or that the EnvironmentMetrics structure will not be added in the future?

(In my mind...I think EnvironmentMetrics is a data structure similar to xxxCollection. It is used in many places and has similar content, but the data sources are different. That's why I have the above suggestions.
